s-fern cs-fern-left"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-row"><picture class="cs-picture"><img alt="Mature landscape cleanup and refresh near NMSU in Las Cruces, NM" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-landscape-maintenance-2.webp" height="477" width="480" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Why University Hills</span><h2 class="cs-title">We Know These Neighborhoods</h2><p class="cs-text">The streets around NMSU are full of 1960s and 1980s ranch-style homes. Many still have bermuda grass lawns that drink water all summer. Older elms, pecans, and mulberries line the yards. Irrigation systems are often 20 to 30 years old. We work in this area every week, so we know the soil, the trees, and the challenges.</p><p class="cs-text">Whether you own a rental near campus or live in Country Club or Telshor, Brainard's Greenscapes can help. We handle lawn-to-xeriscape conversions, tree trimming and removal, irrigation rebuilds, and full landscape installs. Our crew is local, our plants are chosen for this climate, and we show up on time.</p><div class="cs-button-group"><a class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button" href="/contact/">Schedule an Estimate</a> <a class="cs-phone-button" href="tel:575-635-8883"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/phone.svg" height="13" width="13" aria-hidden="true"> (575) 635-8883</a></div></div></div></div></section><section id="areas-services-610"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> What We Do Here</span><h2 class="cs-title">Services Available near NMSU &amp; University Hills</h2></div><div class="cs-grid"><ul class="cs-card-group"><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-landscape-design.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Landscape Design</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Plans sized for compact lots, shade from mature trees, and the tight setbacks common near campus.</p><a class="cs-item-link" href="/services/landscape-design/">Learn More <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-up-right.svg" height="14" width="14" aria-hidden="true"></a></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-landscaping.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Landscaping &amp; Install</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Planting, grading, and full-yard installs built for older properties and small footprints.</p><a class="cs-item-link" href="/services/landscaping/">Learn More <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-up-right.svg" height="14" width="14" aria-hidden="true"></a></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-hardscaping.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Hardscaping &amp; Patios</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Patios, walkways, and retaining walls designed for older homes and monsoon drainage.</p><a class="cs-item-link" href="/services/hardscaping/">Learn More <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-up-right.svg" height="14" width="14" aria-hidden="true"></a></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-xeriscaping.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Xeriscaping</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Replace thirsty bermuda with water-wise plants like Desert Willow, Red Yucca, and Texas Sage.</p><a class="cs-item-link" href="/services/landscaping/xeriscaping/">Learn More <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-up-right.svg" height="14" width="14" aria-hidden="true"></a></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-irrigation.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Irrigation &amp; Sprinkler</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Replace aging sprinkler systems with drip zones and smart controllers that cut water bills.</p><a class="cs-item-link" href="/services/irrigation/">Learn More <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-up-right.svg" height="14" width="14" aria-hidden="true"></a></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-maintenance.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Landscape Maintenance</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Seasonal cleanup, tree pruning, leaf removal, and irrigation checks for homes and rentals.</p><a class="cs-item-link" href="/services/landscape-maintenance/">Learn More <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-up-right.svg" height="14" width="14" aria-hidden="true"></a></li></ul><aside class="cs-area-info"><h3 class="cs-area-title">One Call, One Crew, All Six Services</h3><p class="cs-area-text">Older yards near campus often need several fixes at once: new irrigation, tree work, and a xeriscape conversion. One crew handling all of it saves you time, money, and the hassle of juggling contractors.</p><ul class="cs-area-bullets"><li><span class="cs-check" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="14" viewBox="0 0 14 14" width="14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"><path d="M2 7.5 L5.5 11 L12 3.5"></path></svg> </span>Design-build under one roof</li><li><span class="cs-check" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="14" viewBox="0 0 14 14" width="14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"><path d="M2 7.5 L5.5 11 L12 3.5"></path></svg> </span>Workmanship guarantee</li><li><span class="cs-check" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="14" viewBox="0 0 14 14" width="14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"><path d="M2 7.5 L5.5 11 L12 3.5"></path></svg> </span>Lawn-to-xeriscape conversion pros</li></ul></aside></div></div></section><section id="areas-landmarks-620"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-row"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Where We Work</span><h2 class="cs-title">Neighborhoods &amp; Landmarks We Serve</h2><p class="cs-text">We serve every neighborhood near NMSU, including zip codes <strong>88001</strong> and <strong>88003</strong>. From University Hills to the Country Club area, these streets are close to I-25, downtown, and the university. Each block has its own mix of homes, trees, and yard sizes.</p><div class="cs-button-group"><a class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button" href="/contact/">Schedule an Estimate</a> <a class="cs-phone-button" href="tel:575-635-8883"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/phone.svg" height="13" width="13" aria-hidden="true"> (575) 635-8883</a></div></div><picture class="cs-picture"><img alt="Landscape maintenance and seasonal refresh near NMSU in Las Cruces" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-landscape-maintenance-3.jpeg" height="480" width="580" loading="lazy"></picture></div><ul class="cs-neighborhoods"><li class="cs-neighborhood"><h3 class="cs-neighborhood-title">University Hills <span class="cs-neighborhood-zip">88001</span></h3><p class="cs-neighborhood-text">Ranch-style homes from the 1960s and 1970s with bermuda lawns, aging irrigation, and mature shade trees that need regular care.</p></li><li class="cs-neighborhood"><h3 class="cs-neighborhood-title">University Park <span class="cs-neighborhood-zip">88003</span></h3><p class="cs-neighborhood-text">A mix of faculty homes and student rentals close to campus. Small yards that benefit from low-water, low-maintenance designs.</p></li><li class="cs-neighborhood"><h3 class="cs-neighborhood-title">Alameda Area <span class="cs-neighborhood-zip">88001</span></h3><p class="cs-neighborhood-text">Tree-lined streets with older homes. Pecan and elm roots often interfere with irrigation lines and sewer pipes.</p></li><li class="cs-neighborhood"><h3 class="cs-neighborhood-title">Country Club <span class="cs-neighborhood-zip">88001</span></h3><p class="cs-neighborhood-text">Established neighborhood with larger lots, mature landscaping, and homeowners looking to update tired lawns and patios.</p></li><li class="cs-neighborhood"><h3 class="cs-neighborhood-title">Telshor Area South <span class="cs-neighborhood-zip">88001</span></h3><p class="cs-neighborhood-text">Mid-century homes along the Telshor corridor with wind exposure and full-sun yards that dry out fast in summer.</p></li><li class="cs-neighborhood"><h3 class="cs-neighborhood-title">Campus View <span class="cs-neighborhood-zip">88003</span></h3><p class="cs-neighborhood-text">Rental-heavy blocks just south of NMSU. Property owners want durable, low-maintenance yards that hold up between tenants.</p></li></ul></div></section><section id="services-why-353" class="cs-why-light"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper">Local Know-How</span><h2 class="cs-title">What Makes This Area Different</h2><p class="cs-intro">The neighborhoods around NMSU sit on the valley floor with older infrastructure, compact lots, and decades-old landscaping. Here are the four biggest factors we design around.</p></div><div class="cs-gallery" aria-hidden="true"><picture class="cs-picture cs-picture-1"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-walkways-8.jpeg" height="594" width="460" loading="lazy"></picture><picture class="cs-picture cs-picture-2"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-landscape-maintenance-4.webp" height="439" width="330" loading="lazy"></picture></div><ul class="cs-feature-list"><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">Bermuda &amp; Fescue Lawns</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">These grass types are common here but expensive to keep green. A xeriscape conversion can cut your water bill by 50% or more, and we handle the full process.</p></li><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">Mature Trees &amp; Root Problems</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">Old elms, pecans, and mulberries provide great shade but drop leaves and send roots into clay sewer lines and irrigation pipes. We prune, remove, and reroute as needed.</p></li><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">Aging Irrigation Systems</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">Many systems in this area are 20 to 30 years old with cracked PVC and outdated timers. We rebuild zones, add drip lines, and install smart controllers that save water.</p></li><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">Compact Lots, Creative Design</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">Smaller yards need smart layouts. We use layered plantings, vertical interest, and multi-use hardscape to make every square foot count.</p></li></ul><a class="cs-quote-button" href="/contact/">Schedule an Estimate</a></div></section><section id="testimonials-515" class="cs-reviews-carousel"><picture class="cs-bg-leaves"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/leaves-pattern.jpeg" height="1072" width="1920" loading="lazy"></picture><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Testimonials</span><h2 class="cs-title">Let’s Talk About Your Outdoor Vision</h2></div><div class="cs-controls"><button class="cs-arrow cs-arrow-prev" aria-label="Previous reviews" type="button" data-reviews-prev=""><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M15 18l-6-6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></button> <button class="cs-arrow cs-arrow-next" aria-label="Next reviews" type="button" data-reviews-next=""><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M9 6l6 6-6 6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></button></div></div><ul class="cs-card-group" data-reviews-track=""><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars" role="img"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">David was incredibly knowledgeable and helpful. He patiently answered all of my questions about the plants and trees around my home and provided valuable insights into the issues I was facing. His friendly demeanor and expertise made the experience enjoyable and informative. I highly recommend him</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">Alexis Silva</span> <span class="cs-role">a year ago</span></div><a class="cs-google-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103948667181155023139/reviews" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars" role="img"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">We had a great experience with David. We used him for one of our rental properties in Las Cruces and will definitely be using him again for the next one. Everything from start to finish was professional and timely. Highly recommend.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">Travis Boyle</span> <span class="cs-role">a year ago</span></div><a class="cs-google-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108997149124684397289/reviews" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars" role="img"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">Brainard's Greenscapes recently revamped my backyard with rock landscaping. I couldn't be happier with how the project turned out. From start to finish David's team was