d will be the first one I'll call on any future sprinkler needs.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">Jennifer Wees-Schkade</span> <span class="cs-role">2 years ago</span></div><a class="cs-google-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113879630740524577871/reviews" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars" role="img"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">Brainard’s Greenscapes is a top notch business. I have called on them on several occasions to fix issues with my irrigation system and for new projects. David, the owner, is a sincere, honest individual, who cares about his business and his customers. His employees are also kind and always professional. They are punctual and complete the job as promised and clean up after they are done. I am very pleased with David and his company and have recommended him to my neighbor, who is also a widow because I know he is honest and will not take advantage of her. David is a good guy and I recommend that you give him a call and see for yourself.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">George Rodriguez</span> <span class="cs-role">6 years ago</span></div><a class="cs-google-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113926776793747685994/reviews" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li></ul></div></section><section id="areas-projects-630"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Case Studies</span><h2 class="cs-title">University Hills Project Showcase</h2></div><ul class="cs-project-group"><li class="cs-project"><picture class="cs-project-picture"><img alt="Campus View bermuda-to-xeriscape lawn conversion near NMSU" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-15.webp" height="411" width="616" loading="lazy"></picture><h3 class="cs-project-title">Campus View Lawn Conversion</h3><p class="cs-project-text">A full bermuda-to-xeriscape conversion with drip irrigation, decomposed granite, and native plantings. Water use dropped by more than half.</p></li><li class="cs-project"><picture class="cs-project-picture"><img alt="University Ave commercial landscape refresh in Las Cruces" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-misc-a.jpeg" height="411" width="616" loading="lazy"></picture><h3 class="cs-project-title">University Ave Commercial Refresh</h3><p class="cs-project-text">Low-maintenance commercial landscaping along University Avenue. Gravel beds, hardy shrubs, and clean hardscape edges that look good year-round.</p></li></ul></div></section><section id="faq-506"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> FAQ</span><h2 class="cs-title">University Hills Landscaping FAQ</h2></div><ul class="cs-faq-list"><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">How much water does a grass lawn use vs. xeriscape?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>A bermuda lawn in Las Cruces can use 50 to 60 inches of water per year. A well-designed xeriscape uses about 10 to 15 inches. That means your water bill can drop by half or more after a conversion.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">Can you convert half my yard to xeriscape?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Yes. Many homeowners keep a small patch of grass for kids or pets and convert the rest. We design a clean border between the two zones and set up separate irrigation so each area gets the right amount of water.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">What should I do about tree roots damaging my irrigation?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Older trees like elms and mulberries send roots right through PVC lines. We reroute irrigation around the root zone and use flexible tubing where roots are active. If the tree is too far gone, we can remove it and replant with a less aggressive species.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">Do you work with rental property owners?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Yes. We work with landlords and property managers across the NMSU area. We design yards that are durable, low-maintenance, and easy for tenants to care for. We also offer ongoing maintenance plans so you do not have to rely on tenants for upkeep.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">What are the best low-maintenance plants for a small yard?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>For small lots near NMSU, we recommend Red Yucca, Desert Marigold, Blackfoot Daisy, and Autumn Sage. They stay compact, bloom for months, and need very little water once established. A layer of gravel mulch finishes the look and keeps weeds down.</p></div></details></li></ul></div></section><section id="areas-stats-640"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><div class="cs-heading-col"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Our Coverage Area</span><h2 class="cs-title">Where We Work near NMSU</h2></div><div class="cs-copy-col"><p class="cs-text">On the map below: our coverage around University Hills, University Park, the Alameda area, Country Club, Telshor, and Campus View. We serve every residential and commercial property in this part of Las Cruces.</p><a class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button" href="/contact/">Schedule an Estimate</a></div></div><div class="cs-map" aria-label="Map of University Hills and NMSU area in Las Cruces, NM"><iframe allowfullscreen="" height="430" loading="lazy" referrerpolicy="no-referrer-when-downgrade" src="https://www.google.com/maps?q=University+Hills+Las+Cruces+NM&amp;z=14&amp;output=embed" title="Map of University Hills and NMSU area in Las Cruces, NM" width="1280"></iframe></div><ul class="cs-stats"><li class="cs-stat"><span class="cs-stat-number">500+</span> <span class="cs-stat-label">Las Cruces Projects</span></li><li class="cs-stat"><span class="cs-stat-number">19+</span> <span class="cs-stat-label">Years in the Valley</span></li><li class="cs-stat"><span class="cs-stat-number">5/5</span> <span class="cs-stat-label">Average Rating</span></li><li class="cs-stat"><span class="cs-stat-number">100%</span> <span class="cs-stat-label">Quality Guarantee</span></li></ul></div></section><section id="areas-neighbors-660"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Nearby</span><h2 class="cs-title">Neighboring Areas We Serve</h2><p class="cs-text">We also handle landscape projects in nearby Mesilla Valley communities just minutes away.</p></div><ul class="cs-neighbors"><li class="cs-neighbor"><a class="cs-neighbor-link" href="/service-areas/las-cruces-nm/"><span class="cs-neighbor-name">Landscapi